Articles.Content:
I've downloaded this mod + the textures, and installed into a fresh copy of 1.31. However, when I load KSP no dice, it's still the same old KSP solar system.

 

Thoughts? Never had a mod "not" install like this.

39 minutes ago, Kokanee said:

I've downloaded this mod + the textures, and installed into a fresh copy of 1.31. However, when I load KSP no dice, it's still the same old KSP solar system.

 

Thoughts? Never had a mod "not" install like this.

Gonna needs logs, and screenshot of your gamedata folder. Also, if this is a 100% fresh install, you need to run the game once without mods so KSP can build its settings.

1 hour ago, Galileo said:

 Also, if this is a 100% fresh install, you need to run the game once without mods so KSP can build its settings.

I'll try wiping everything, fresh install, run once then install RSS thanks for the tip.
No dice, here is my gamedata folder (https://imgur.com/a/P9Q5x) and I've uploaded my ksp.log file here: http://www.mediafire.com/file/m0vf9q84tlr1mwr/KSP.log

32 minutes ago, Kokanee said:

No dice, here is my gamedata folder (https://imgur.com/a/P9Q5x) and I've uploaded my ksp.log file here: http://www.mediafire.com/file/m0vf9q84tlr1mwr/KSP.log

 

 

 

Are you using the Kopernicus that comes included in the RSS download? If so, it won’t work. I think you are because module manager 2.8.0 does not work with 1.3.1. Also Kopernicus is version locked. The version included with RSS is for KSP 1.2.2 and will only work with 1.2.2. You need to be using Kopernicus 1.3.1-3. And the latest module manager. There is also a patch in the RSS thread that I posted that makes RSS compatible with 1.3.1. You will need to go through the last couple of pages to find it.
Thanks for the swift reply, much appreciated.

4 hours ago, Galileo said:

Just use Kerbal konstructs and place another runway next to the stock one.

I didn't even think about taking that route. As far as you know, is there anything out of the ordinary that is needed to make parts built for Kerbal Konstructs work on a real-sized Earth? I've never actually modded anything into the game before (not even a MM patch), so I'm ignorant of the rules and regulations.
When I try to use this mod, the oceans disappear unless i zoom way out and scatterer and EVE no longer work

On 2/15/2018 at 10:25 AM, Ekircher5 said:

When I try to use this mod, the oceans disappear unless i zoom way out and scatterer and EVE no longer work

Are you using RSSVE? RSSVE has the profiles that allow EVE and Scatterer to work with RSS; without it, you won't have much, if any, change from the stock graphics.

On 2/14/2018 at 6:34 PM, fallout2077 said:

I didn't even think about taking that route. As far as you know, is there anything out of the ordinary that is needed to make parts built for Kerbal Konstructs work on a real-sized Earth? I've never actually modded anything into the game before (not even a MM patch), so I'm ignorant of the rules and regulations.

The runway models are already available in Kerbal konstructs, you don’t have to model anything. You just have to put it where you want it. Kk is really simple and easy to use

The runway models are already available in Kerbal konstructs, you don’t have to model anything. You just have to put it where you want it. Kk is really simple and easy to use

Oh well, I'll have to tinker around more with it. Thanks for the assistance, @Galileo
